    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>From a lambda, you can't get a reference to anything that isn't final. You need to declare a final wrapper from outside the lambda to hold your variable.</p>\n<p>I've added the final 'reference' object as this wrapper.</p>\n<pre><code>private TimeZone extractCalendarTimeZoneComponent(Calendar cal,TimeZone calTz) {\n    final AtomicReference&lt;TimeZone&gt; reference = new AtomicReference&lt;&gt;();\n\n    try {\n       cal.getComponents().getComponents(&quot;VTIMEZONE&quot;).forEach(component-&gt;{\n        VTimeZone v = (VTimeZone) component;\n           v.getTimeZoneId();\n           if(reference.get()==null) {\n               reference.set(TimeZone.getTimeZone(v.getTimeZoneId().getValue()));\n           }\n           });\n    } catch (Exception e) {\n        //log.warn(&quot;Unable to determine ical timezone&quot;, e);\n    }\n    return reference.get();\n}   \n</code></pre>\n"
  }, {
