      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
      "body" : "Good answer +1, and I&#39;m surprised by how little coverage the <i>reason</i> for effectively final seems to get.  Of note: A local variable can only be captured by a lambda if it is <i>also</i> definitely assigned before the body of the lambda.  Both requirements would seem to ensure that accessing the local variable would be thread safe."
