      "body" : "@Vince I don&#39;t think allowing passing class member variables into lambda expressions is due to the memory model. It is just because <code>this</code> pointer is final. See <a href=\"https://stackoverflow.com/questions/4732544/why-are-only-final-variables-accessible-in-anonymous-class\" title=\"why are only final variables accessible in anonymous class\">stackoverflow.com/questions/4732544/&hellip;</a>"
